{
  "name": "Dwarf Planet Size Density/Gravity",
  "formula": "1d100",
  "description": "<p>Use this oracle to define the main attributes of a planetary body. Once you roll for the world size, roll its density to determine the gravity.</p><p>Gravities</p><ul><li>None: This celestial body has no gravity. Mechanical aids are required to traverse its environment.</li><li>Little: Gravitational forces are so feeble that they cannot provide consistent traction. Mechanical aids are recommended.</li><li>Weak: With enough caution and consideration, greatly reduced gravitational forces allow for major freedom of movement.</li><li>Low: Reduced gravity allows for significant maneuverability.</li><li>Ideal: Gravitational forces are at the levels to which humans naturally evolved to thrive.</li><li>High: Human survival can only be maintained for short durations without mechanical aids.</li><li>Severe:Explorers are unable to survive this level of gravity without the assistance of mechanical aids.</li></ul>",
